28/04/22, 12:15 am - Anusha Sharma: https://www.sih.gov.in/sih2022PS?technology_bucket=QWxs&category=U29mdHdhcmU=&organization=QWxs&organization_type=QWxs
28/04/22, 12:30 am - Shreyansh: Background: Passwords are ubiquitous today on any platform, on possibly any website. But to remember so difficult passwords and that too on numerous websites seems daunting and therefore you can devise a project illustrating graphical password strategy. This will allow the user to set passwords in the form of graphical presentation in a certain pattern and later use that pattern to login o the system. Summary: Remembering numerous passwords from various different sites can be difficult for a user. So to provide some flexibility we can provide users a graphical password authentication system where instead of creating a password a user has to select graphical objects in a particular order to keep it as their password. Objective: : In this method, the user is required to select some images (let’s say different chocolates) in a specific pattern (for example dairy milk is followed by 5 stars which is in turn followed by KitKat and so on). Next time the user tries to log in, the images would have been shuffled, but the user will be required to follow the same pattern which was used initially. Every time the user will have to use the same sequence while the images are placed in different ways. This type of authentication is difficult to break since neither brute force nor dictionary attacks could breach it. We need techniques that can be easily implemented and provide better results to this process.

28/04/22, 1:21 am - Anusha Sharma: Any business with an online presence - even those which are not actually selling goods or services on their website - must include certain details in order to abide by the Electronic Commerce Regulations, such as full company details. Website terms and conditions are the best places to include such information. As stated earlier, ALL websites interact with user data in some way. This means that if you have a website and you intend to have people visit that website, then it's mandatory that you include a privacy policy. The law requires you to inform users about what data you collect, how it's used, stored and protected.Data breaches and attacks on personal information by sites is not a new thing. Often such sites do not have proper terms and condition and they take advantage of no tool to detect this and steal data and cause threat. Addressing this problem will help in having a tool which checks the Terms and Condition and generates report of the issues found. There is a requirement of a tool(Web,App,Standalone tool) which checks the terms and conditions, privacy policies, cookies of any mobile application(Android/IOS/Web App/web pages) and shows the necessary details in the report for the required authorities to take action.1. How can digital means help checking of terms and conditions, privacy policies, cookies of apps that are detrimental to data security and cyber security? For example, there can be a python based tool which checks the terms and conditions, privacy policies, cookies of any mobile application and generates a report of the same.

29/04/22, 10:30 pm - Anusha Sharma: We, the team ScholarWings is going to build a platform to connect the several agencies that gives funding under various schemes and the the needy students as well as higher educational institutions. We will be having four portals on our platform that are: 1. Stating of problem statement by the needy students or HEIs. 2. Inforamation about the fund granters. 3. Filtering the granters and takers according to their needs by the help of smart filtering technology using AI. 4. Progress report of students project and the part of fund granted to them by the granters. There is no platform that can bring together all large and relevant project funding schemes to one place, check their legitimacy, and disclose their previous funding history.​Up to now there has been no site that matches the fund granters and takers according to their subjected requirements with the help of AI based smart filter technology.​There is no such platform that connects current students in need of funds with previous beneficiaries of schemes. ​The current systems for this purpose have a poor user interface and are inaccessible.​There is no portal which tracks project's progress and part of fund delivered for students and sponsors.​Platforms that meet these demands are either paid or don't cater to Indian students.​There is no platform which not only connects funders and also showcase top projects to help them gain popularity and support from industries.​
Our basic approach would be to work towards a better user interface for better user experience. This we will do by dividing schemes into categories for more personalized and efficient search with the help of AI based technology. We will be working towards easy one-time documentation process so that the student don't need to go through tedious process of uploading documents again and again. We will be verifying various funding schemes to counter fraud funding. We want to create a space that not only gives them the funding but also nurtures their projects as well as fund receiver's and granter's relationships for further helps. We will be using AI, Machine Learning, HTML, CSS, JAVA Script, Firebase, Figma and Bootstrap to build our platform. 
Now coming towards the most exciting and awaited part of our project that is business potential in our project. So the main idea is to invite companies that manufacture or sell hardware or software solutions required by the students for their projects so that the companies can advertise their products to their targeted audience through our portal and for these tailored advertising services we can charge them. ​We on our portal will showcase top ongoing and completed projects to inspire students who visit the portal and to attract the funding agencies.​

30/06/22, 10:03 pm - Shreyansh: Good evening everyone,
I am shreyansh jain from gwalior, Madhya Pradesh,
I currently pursuing btech in computer science and engineering from National institute of technology, hamirpur

 My skills includes native Android development in java and Kotlin.

My past experiences includes Android developer in careerguide.com and Android developer in cogent web services.

My projects includes Feedtheneed, auto vibratemode, subalsangam, nithapp etc.

I volunteered in Google developer students club as a Android team member.


Auto vibratemode is a location based Android application which helps to turn our Android phone to vibration mode where we want it to stay undisturbed. As a employee it requires that our phone will not ring in between meetings and as a student we require to keep our phone silent in classes. To solve this we come up with auto vibratemode. 
We once have to save the location where we want our phone to be silent, then everytime we reach about 50m radius circle of that location,it will turn it to vibration.
